|YKB                        MONK BASICS
|GKB~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ 

|YK0                    "Look within. Be still."
|YK0                         -Zen saying

|CK0  Make no mistake, the life of a monk is not easy. When you took
|CK0  the vow to become a monk, it was a serious one. Monks live a
|CK0  solitary life, unable to marry or swear an oath.

|CK0  Monks are without worldly possessions; monks cannot own boats,
|CK0  nor have any level of wealth beyond the very basics needed.

|CK0  Monks live to train. Monks have at their disposal an array of 
|CK0  skills, spells, and attacks, many of which at the pinnacle of
|CK0  training, can do some impressive things.

|CK0  Monks rely on their own sense of chi. A monk's chi is essential
|CK0  to everything they do - from basic combat, to strengthening
|CK0  and hardening their own body through the staff soul, to unleashing
|CK0  chi-based attacks on their opponents. But, like everything in life, chi
|CK0  must be maintained and guided. Without attention, a monk's chi
|CK0  will drain and drift away.

|CK0  Modern monk combat is not about isolated skills. It is built on
|CK0  rhythm. Openers generate tags and momentum, finishers cash that
|CK0  pressure in, and bridge techniques carry your chain from one style
|CK0  into another without forcing a reset.

|CK0  Use "mskills" to see what each technique is for, and "mcombo" to
|CK0  see your current combo state and route guidance.

|CK0  Monks earn Monk XP in battle. It advances guild level automatically,
|CK0  but the road to mastery still passes through formal challenges at
|CK0  guild levels 4, 9, 14, and 19. Monk XP earned while a challenge or
|CK0  regular level blocks advancement remains banked.

|CK0  Use "msc" or "gscore Monk" to review your progress. The "cost" and
|CK0  "advance guild" commands explain the next gate but never spend ordinary
|CK0  experience.

|CK0  On the surface, monks are but a ripple on the water. But, as
|CK0  that ripple carries, so it grows. 

